docs.abstract: A judge has blocked the U.S. from transferring an American citizen, held in Iraq for seven months as an “enemy combatant,” to the custody of another country.
docs.snippet: A judge has blocked the U.S. from transferring an American citizen, held in Iraq for seven months as an “enemy combatant,” to the custody of another country.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A federal judge blocked the Trump administration on Thursday from transferring an American citizen detainee — who has already been held in Iraq as a suspected Islamic State member for seven months — to the custody of another country against his will.

headline.main: Judge Halts Transfer of American ISIS Suspect to Other Country
headline.print_headline: Judge Blocks Bid to Move A U.S. Citizen Held in Iraq

docs.abstract: With the backing of Senator Heidi Heitkamp, Mike Pompeo looks assured to become secretary of state, but the Foreign Relations Committee may withhold its support.
docs.snippet: With the backing of Senator Heidi Heitkamp, Mike Pompeo looks assured to become secretary of state, but the Foreign Relations Committee may withhold its support.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Mike Pompeo came close on Thursday to clinching confirmation as the nation’s 70th secretary of state when Senator Heidi Heitkamp, Democrat of North Dakota, announced her support. But before that triumph, he is expected to face a historic rebuke from the Senate Foreign Relations Committee, which most likely will not recommend his confirmation.

headline.main: Pompeo Nears Confirmation but Faces Historic Rebuke From Committee
headline.print_headline: Hint of Snub For Pompeo, On His Way To Approval

byline.original: By Nicholas Fandos and Gardiner Harris

docs.abstract: The American-led air campaign to defeat the remnants of ISIS in eastern Syria lost its main ground force. Now it is shifting its tactics to kill the last remaining fighters.
docs.snippet: The American-led air campaign to defeat the remnants of ISIS in eastern Syria lost its main ground force. Now it is shifting its tactics to kill the last remaining fighters.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The United States-led air campaign to hunt down the last pockets of Islamic State militants in eastern Syria effectively ground to a halt in the past two months after the allies lost their most effective battleground partner, stalling a critical phase of the offensive.

headline.main: American Warplanes Shift Tactics to Target Last ISIS Pockets in Eastern Syria
headline.print_headline: U.S. Warplanes Shift Tactics to Target Last ISIS Pockets in Eastern Syria

docs.abstract: Education Secretary Betsy DeVos will defend her agency’s budget before a House panel, including a reorganization plan that staff members say she tried to withhold from Congress.
docs.snippet: Education Secretary Betsy DeVos will defend her agency’s budget before a House panel, including a reorganization plan that staff members say she tried to withhold from Congress.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Education Secretary Betsy DeVos will go before a House panel on Tuesday to defend her agency’s budget, including a sweeping overhaul of the Education Department that has strained relations within her agency and with Congress — and defies the White House’s budget office.

headline.main: As DeVos Faces Congress, Officials Say She Hid Plans to Overhaul Department

docs.abstract: In a farewell speech, Secretary of State Rex W. Tillerson urged respect and civility in a time and town where he was fired by a presidential Twitter post.
docs.snippet: In a farewell speech, Secretary of State Rex W. Tillerson urged respect and civility in a time and town where he was fired by a presidential Twitter post.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Secretary of State Rex W. Tillerson bade farewell to the State Department on Thursday in a brief and barbed speech that called for an era of respect and kindness after he was dismissed by presidential tweet.

headline.main: Tillerson Says Goodbye to ‘a Very Mean-Spirited Town’
headline.print_headline: To a ‘Mean-Spirited Town,’ Tillerson Counsels Respect and Kindness

docs.abstract: The special counsel is emphasizing his lack of independence to defend the indictment of Paul Manafort, President Trump’s former campaign chairman.
docs.snippet: The special counsel is emphasizing his lack of independence to defend the indictment of Paul Manafort, President Trump’s former campaign chairman.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Robert S. Mueller III, the special counsel investigating Russia’s interference in the 2016 election, transformed this week what has appeared to be a weakness — his relative lack of independence — into a strength.

headline.main: For Mueller, a Feared Weakness Becomes a Strength
headline.print_headline: A Mueller Weakness Becomes a Strength

docs.abstract: The measure is part of a sweeping deregulatory agenda that includes several rules and regulations for the department to scrap or amend.
docs.snippet: The measure is part of a sweeping deregulatory agenda that includes several rules and regulations for the department to scrap or amend.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Education Secretary Betsy DeVos, a lifelong advocate of Christian education, moved on Wednesday to loosen federal regulations on religious colleges and universities, after a Supreme Court decision that restricted states from denying some kinds of aid to religious institutions.

headline.main: DeVos Moves to Loosen Restrictions on Federal Aid to Religious Colleges
headline.print_headline: DeVos Pushes Federal Aid For Religious Universities

docs.abstract: The president announced the summit meeting’s date and place in a Twitter post hours after meeting the three Americans freed by North Korea at Joint Base Andrews.
docs.snippet: The president announced the summit meeting’s date and place in a Twitter post hours after meeting the three Americans freed by North Korea at Joint Base Andrews.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump, exulting in the release of three Americans from prison in North Korea, confirmed Thursday that he would meet Kim Jong-un, the North’s leader, in Singapore on June 12, setting the date for a once unimaginable encounter.

headline.main: Trump Exults in Release of Prisoners and a Date Next Month With Kim Jong-un
headline.print_headline: Trump to Meet  Kim for Talks In Singapore

docs.abstract: Senator Richard M. Burr of North Carolina, the chairman of the Senate Intelligence Committee, said he saw “no reason to dispute” the findings of the United States’ spy agencies.
docs.snippet: Senator Richard M. Burr of North Carolina, the chairman of the Senate Intelligence Committee, said he saw “no reason to dispute” the findings of the United States’ spy agencies.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Republican at the helm of the Senate’s investigation into Russian interference in the 2016 presidential election backed on Wednesday the assessment by American intelligence agencies that Moscow favored Donald J. Trump in the race, contradicting both the president and fellow Republicans in the House.

headline.main: Top Republican Senator Says ‘No Reason to Dispute’ That Russia Favored Trump
headline.print_headline: Top Republican Senator Says There’s ‘No Doubt’ Russia Favored Trump

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump and his critics actually agree on something. If a column he read in a magazine is correct, he wrote on Twitter on Thursday, “this is bigger than Watergate!”
